<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="484" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6193/11–1948: Airgram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-19">November 19,
                                1948</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A–234. On behalf of another agency of the government please submit any
                            additional information not already reported concerning the recent
                            activities of Soviet Ambassador Roschin, especially in regard <pb facs="0602" n="592" xml:id="pg_592"/> to discussions he is reported
                            to have held with high officials in the Ministry of Defense and the
                            Ministry of Foreign Affairs of China.</p>
                        <p>This request has also been addressed to the Department of the Army and
                            Navy and may have been referred by them to their representatives at
                            Nanking.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>